title: Graustock
text:
The Graustock is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a> of the <a href="Urner%20Alps">Urner Alps</a>, located south of <a href="Engelberg">Engelberg</a> in <a href="Central%20Switzerland">Central Switzerland</a>. The summit is one of the two <a href="tripoint">tripoint</a>s between the cantons of <a href="Canton%20of%20Berne">Berne</a>, <a href="Nidwalden">Nidwalden</a> and <a href="Obwalden">Obwalden</a> (the other being the <a href="Jochstock">Jochstock</a>).
On the north side of the mountain lies the <a href="Tr%C3%BCebsee">Trüebsee</a>.
